WEBVTT

00:06.042 --> 00:07.281
I heard about Kev.

00:07.366 --> 00:08.844
You don't know
what really happened.

00:08.929 --> 00:11.141
- No?
- You didn't shoot and kill

00:11.250 --> 00:12.344
my baby brother?

00:12.429 --> 00:13.843
Kev was my family, too,

00:13.945 --> 00:15.032
and I ain't got much left.

00:15.117 --> 00:17.204
We can squash this beef here,
right now.

00:17.306 --> 00:18.398
<i>He's gonna use his connect</i>

00:18.483 --> 00:19.666
to start at ten keys a week.

00:19.751 --> 00:21.251
So you got him
making money for you now?

00:21.335 --> 00:22.419
Makes the world go round.

00:22.521 --> 00:24.063
- And you trust him?
- End of the day,

00:24.148 --> 00:25.782
he just want to look out
for his family.

00:25.867 --> 00:27.539
<i>I want to buy directly from you.</i>

00:27.624 --> 00:28.836
Franklin know about this?

00:28.982 --> 00:30.046
No.

00:30.162 --> 00:31.461
Franklin is the answer.

00:31.609 --> 00:34.023
In the end, only he can bring
your enemies down.

00:34.156 --> 00:35.430
There's gonna be a wedding.

00:37.599 --> 00:40.359
Did you dose everybody
with LSD?

00:43.174 --> 00:45.774
You can't be a gangster
and a family man.

00:45.878 --> 00:47.429
In the end, you'll have
to destroy us all.

00:47.513 --> 00:49.446
And all you
have to offer is lies.

00:49.548 --> 00:50.780
Dripped with honey.

00:50.883 --> 00:52.849
You think
you have to kill me one day.

00:52.951 --> 00:54.782
But before you do,
I'm gonna kill you.

00:54.867 --> 00:56.871
There's only one
thing you really need to know.

00:56.955 --> 00:58.485
Once you press that button,

00:58.570 --> 01:00.090
there's no turning back.

01:00.192 --> 01:02.159
<i> You were
right, I should've listened.</i>

01:02.261 --> 01:03.845
<i>I should've treated you
like a partner.</i>

01:03.929 --> 01:06.015
<i>You know, it's not too late.</i>

01:06.406 --> 01:07.688
It is.

01:07.773 --> 01:10.507
<i>I've got to follow
my own path now.</i>

01:46.344 --> 01:47.376
Hey.

01:49.078 --> 01:51.078
How you holding up?

01:52.227 --> 01:54.161
How would you be?

01:55.109 --> 01:57.203
Kovatch is itching
to talk to you.

01:57.288 --> 01:58.960
Thought maybe
you'd want to run me through

01:59.045 --> 02:00.648
what happened here first.

02:06.015 --> 02:07.539
You know, we got a tip that

02:07.624 --> 02:10.382
<i>cocaine was being sold out
of the pool hall, so we came</i>

02:10.467 --> 02:12.167
<i>to check it out.</i>

02:14.917 --> 02:17.054
<i>They just started shooting.</i>

02:17.230 --> 02:18.596
Oh, shit, five-o!

02:20.888 --> 02:22.448
<i>And how'd you
end up in the back?</i>

02:22.734 --> 02:24.434
<i>One of them ran.</i>

02:25.695 --> 02:27.406
<i>I warned him repeatedly to stop.</i>

02:27.491 --> 02:28.921
<i>Damn, bruh!</i>

02:29.023 --> 02:31.234
<i>He had a gun in his hand.</i>

02:31.319 --> 02:33.219
Aah!

02:34.098 --> 02:36.265
<i>He was turning back to fire.</i>

02:38.312 --> 02:39.990
<i>And, uh...</i>

02:40.099 --> 02:42.456
<i>11-99. Perez is hit!</i>

02:42.541 --> 02:44.274
<i>Repeat, Perez is down!</i>

02:47.820 --> 02:49.854
That's when I saw him.

02:57.743 --> 03:00.377
Okay.

03:01.194 --> 03:03.632
Kovatch is gonna want
to hear that from you.

03:03.984 --> 03:05.998
Then you got to go in,

03:06.083 --> 03:07.983
give an official statement.

03:12.570 --> 03:14.448
Hey, the guy in the back.

03:14.533 --> 03:15.932
He make it?

03:16.522 --> 03:18.328
He's barely hanging on.

03:18.413 --> 03:20.054
Took him over to king.

03:27.274 --> 03:29.274
<font color=#FF00FF>*SNOWFALL*</font>
<font color=#00FF00>Season 05  Episode 09</font>

03:29.358 --> 03:30.940
Episode Title: <font color=#FFc30f>"Departures"</font>
Aired on: <font color="#00ffff">April 13, 2022.</font>

04:10.144 --> 04:11.468
Who?

04:13.687 --> 04:15.351
Oh, oh, yeah.

04:15.436 --> 04:16.921
Yeah, send him up.

04:17.983 --> 04:19.507
Thanks.

04:30.442 --> 04:32.554
- What's up?
- Sup?

04:33.046 --> 04:34.304
Welcome.

04:40.780 --> 04:42.070
Shit.

04:46.258 --> 04:48.125
Look at this place.

04:51.166 --> 04:53.062
Been meaning to have you over.

04:54.066 --> 04:56.007
Been paging you all morning.

04:57.101 --> 04:58.859
Yeah.

04:58.944 --> 05:00.859
Couldn't sleep, man.

05:01.286 --> 05:03.719
You know, mind was
just racing on me.

05:04.462 --> 05:06.296
Feel like I've been carved out.

05:06.515 --> 05:08.812
I was actually feeling
pretty good.

05:10.007 --> 05:12.141
Went to the crib,
poured a drink.

05:12.226 --> 05:14.453
Watched the sun rise
on the roof.

05:14.687 --> 05:17.020
Like I finally knew
what I had to do.

05:17.333 --> 05:20.226
Then I got word cops hit
the pool hall.

05:20.789 --> 05:22.445
Three of Kane people dead.

05:22.530 --> 05:23.909
Kane in surgery.

05:24.129 --> 05:25.996
Want to guess who it was?

05:26.648 --> 05:28.131
Hmm?

05:30.007 --> 05:31.534
She lied to us.

05:32.171 --> 05:33.269
Said shit was fine.

05:33.354 --> 05:35.487
And went behind our backs
and hit 'em anyway.

05:37.309 --> 05:39.576
What you want me
to do about it, Lee?

05:40.265 --> 05:41.695
What?

05:44.066 --> 05:46.109
What would you like me to do?

05:47.687 --> 05:49.419
Yell and scream?

05:50.328 --> 05:51.937
Shoot up the club?

05:52.079 --> 05:54.429
Go to war with Louie and Jerome?

05:54.717 --> 05:56.593
- The cops?
- There's what's right

05:56.764 --> 05:58.455
and there's what's wrong,
and this shit is wrong.

05:58.539 --> 06:00.697
Yeah, well,
Kane tried to kill us.

06:00.799 --> 06:02.032
Jerome and Louie hit back.

06:02.134 --> 06:03.233
We made a deal with Kane.

06:03.342 --> 06:05.389
That's what's right
in our world.

06:05.570 --> 06:07.771
I ain't saying
I'm happy with any of it.

06:09.007 --> 06:10.206
But there's other shit that's

06:10.308 --> 06:11.490
more important to me, man.

06:11.575 --> 06:13.043
Like what?

06:13.145 --> 06:15.178
Like surviving.

06:16.604 --> 06:19.529
Surviving to take care
of my unborn baby.

06:20.598 --> 06:22.831
Like not going to war
with my family.

06:24.948 --> 06:26.614
I can't tell you
what to do any more

06:26.699 --> 06:28.666
than I can Jerome and Louie.

06:28.894 --> 06:30.373
That's a first.

06:32.074 --> 06:34.008
But I ain't going out a martyr.

06:35.506 --> 06:36.900
Nah, you're going out here.

06:37.881 --> 06:38.961
In your Wilshire penthouse.

06:39.123 --> 06:40.904
Look, if...

06:41.397 --> 06:42.904
If you're trying
to make me feel bad,

06:42.989 --> 06:44.959
that's not the way, all right?

06:45.210 --> 06:47.610
Now, you want to fight this,
be my guest.

06:47.939 --> 06:49.939
But I won't be there.

06:56.810 --> 06:58.843
You ain't even open it, huh?

07:12.818 --> 07:14.651
You are so beautiful.

07:19.352 --> 07:21.311
Was it everything
that you wanted?

07:21.432 --> 07:23.465
Mm-hmm.

07:24.172 --> 07:25.405
All that

07:25.507 --> 07:27.803
and a chocolate fountain of LSD.

07:29.842 --> 07:31.508
Probably skully.

07:31.682 --> 07:33.314
- Yeah.
- Mm-hmm.

07:33.399 --> 07:35.217
It probably was.

07:35.430 --> 07:37.725
That shit could've gone
all wrong.

07:38.061 --> 07:39.165
Yeah.

07:39.250 --> 07:40.748
But it didn't.

07:42.042 --> 07:43.850
Maybe it's a good omen.

07:44.244 --> 07:45.725
Mm-hmm.

07:47.061 --> 07:49.714
Word's probably out
about Kane by now.

07:50.899 --> 07:52.350
I know.

07:53.544 --> 07:55.467
Checked my pager this morning.

07:55.583 --> 07:58.904
- And?
- Five missed from Leon.

08:01.495 --> 08:04.029
I wish we could just stay
in bed all day.

08:06.529 --> 08:08.296
We can.

08:09.013 --> 08:10.936
- We can?
- Mm-hmm.

08:11.104 --> 08:13.738
- We can.
- Let's just stay in bed all day.

08:13.840 --> 08:15.639
Yeah.

08:18.378 --> 08:20.611
Oh, no.

08:22.266 --> 08:23.693
No.

08:23.778 --> 08:26.078
Shit needs to be dealt with.

08:26.443 --> 08:28.486
I'll tell you what.

08:28.850 --> 08:31.522
- I'll call downstairs.
- Mm-hmm?

08:31.607 --> 08:33.272
Extend our stay

08:33.668 --> 08:35.833
till Wednesday before the trip.

08:37.475 --> 08:39.981
Then we come back here
later tonight.

08:41.900 --> 08:44.374
I like it.

08:44.459 --> 08:46.337
You ever gonna tell me
where we going?

08:46.748 --> 08:48.309
I mean, you're gonna know
in a few days,

08:48.408 --> 08:49.225
that's all I know.

08:49.310 --> 08:51.277
You just like seeing me squirm,
that's all.

08:51.407 --> 08:53.007
I fucking love you.

08:53.289 --> 08:56.097
- I love you.
- I like it when you say that.

08:56.325 --> 08:57.968
Say it again.

08:58.251 --> 09:00.651
- You like it?
- Mm-hmm.

09:06.867 --> 09:09.000
Anything else I should know?

09:09.399 --> 09:10.983
Um...

09:11.358 --> 09:13.257
No, it's all there.

09:13.779 --> 09:15.326
Just like I said.

09:15.411 --> 09:17.252
And the cocaine
you got the tip about

09:17.337 --> 09:19.370
in the first place?

09:20.182 --> 09:22.217
Bad information, right?

09:23.476 --> 09:24.990
It happens.

09:25.075 --> 09:26.936
yeah?

09:27.981 --> 09:29.303
Come on in.

09:38.514 --> 09:41.192
Kind of need to pull
a tube of blood, detective.

09:41.592 --> 09:42.983
Are you serious?

09:43.068 --> 09:45.178
As of right now,
you are suspended,

09:45.263 --> 09:46.399
pending results

09:46.484 --> 09:48.584
of I.A.'s investigation
into the shooting

09:48.681 --> 09:50.214
and these test results.

09:50.299 --> 09:52.381
So you tell us to clean shit up,

09:52.670 --> 09:55.076
and suddenly you give
a fuck about how it gets done?

09:55.161 --> 09:57.128
An officer is dead,
and I want to know why.

09:57.213 --> 09:58.818
Or is it just me, huh?

09:59.913 --> 10:02.213
'Cause I ain't some six-foot-two

10:02.315 --> 10:03.865
square-jawed southern boy.

10:03.950 --> 10:05.217
"Yes, sir, no, sir,

10:05.302 --> 10:07.537
shine your shoes for you, sir?"

10:13.138 --> 10:15.171
I shine my own shoes.

10:16.644 --> 10:18.747
And I clean up after myself.

10:18.964 --> 10:20.997
You should've done the same.

10:27.302 --> 10:29.449
Fuck this. I want my union rep.

10:29.534 --> 10:31.134
I want my fucking lawyer
in here.

10:31.244 --> 10:32.710
Refuse to cooperate,
and there'll be

10:32.812 --> 10:35.374
criminal charges to go
along with the disgrace.

10:35.459 --> 10:36.803
In the meantime, I'm gonna need

10:36.895 --> 10:38.787
your gun and badge, detective.

10:44.733 --> 10:46.524
All right.

10:55.492 --> 10:57.615
I know you
don't want to hear it, but...

10:59.234 --> 11:01.740
...I understand
why Louie did what she did.

11:05.040 --> 11:07.207
Right thing, the wrong way.

11:10.990 --> 11:13.678
Who doses an entire wedding?

11:14.058 --> 11:16.959
What if I'd have stayed,
huh, eaten a strawberry?

11:17.044 --> 11:19.111
I don't even want
to think about it.

11:20.459 --> 11:21.967
You could've called me,
you know.

11:22.052 --> 11:23.779
If you were in such bad shape.

11:25.532 --> 11:27.233
Oh, we talked.

11:28.440 --> 11:30.764
Had a whole conversation.

11:33.490 --> 11:34.972
Hmm.

11:35.074 --> 11:36.811
What did we talk about?

11:38.511 --> 11:40.420
Hey, you want
to get out of here?

11:40.505 --> 11:42.505
Like, leave town?

11:43.717 --> 11:45.483
I just want to clear my head.

11:46.709 --> 11:48.619
What'd you have in mind?

11:55.423 --> 11:57.451
You shaved your beard.

11:57.880 --> 11:59.623
In light of last night,
I thought

11:59.837 --> 12:02.100
it would be helpful
to alter my appearance.

12:02.638 --> 12:04.238
I was thinking those things
you were saying

12:04.322 --> 12:05.720
are closer to the truth
than not.

12:05.805 --> 12:07.038
I was drugged.

12:07.170 --> 12:09.873
I was scared.
Fuck, I'm still scared.

12:10.186 --> 12:11.428
I'm sorry.

12:11.513 --> 12:13.506
You know what you should be
scared of, cissy?

12:14.514 --> 12:16.186
What the CIA is gonna do

12:16.271 --> 12:18.204
to your son if I don't help you.

12:18.951 --> 12:20.873
Because when they're done
with him,

12:21.084 --> 12:22.386
they will kill him.

12:22.488 --> 12:23.748
That's a fact.

12:23.833 --> 12:26.234
Right now you think
you have two bad choices.

12:26.461 --> 12:29.562
But I'm the only hope you have
to save Franklin.

12:33.998 --> 12:36.732
Ana told me what you were like
when she recruited you.

12:37.522 --> 12:38.936
Alone.

12:39.108 --> 12:41.162
Desperate to find a
man who was gone forever.

12:41.247 --> 12:42.502
Okay.
I don't need to be

12:42.587 --> 12:44.916
- reminded of that right now.
- No, I think you do.

12:45.963 --> 12:48.502
And I think you need to put away
these childish excuses

12:48.587 --> 12:50.465
if you want to have
any hope of killing Teddy

12:50.550 --> 12:53.275
- and getting you out of this alive.
- Wait a goddamn second.

12:53.360 --> 12:55.303
Short of incriminating
my own son,

12:55.388 --> 12:57.121
I have done everything

12:57.223 --> 12:58.489
that you have asked me to do.

12:58.666 --> 12:59.869
You, on the other hand,

12:59.954 --> 13:01.809
have given me
no reason to believe

13:01.894 --> 13:04.495
that you can do what you said
you were gonna do.

13:05.041 --> 13:06.831
Now, both Teddy's drug runner

13:06.933 --> 13:08.760
and gun supplier
were there yesterday.

13:09.327 --> 13:11.361
Tell me you got something
we can use.

13:12.733 --> 13:15.603
Could've gotten more
if you had kept your head.

13:17.525 --> 13:18.955
But yes.

13:19.458 --> 13:21.674
Ultimately,
it was incredibly helpful.

13:22.414 --> 13:24.348
My people are digging
into Gustavo zapata

13:24.433 --> 13:26.345
and avi drexler as we speak.

13:29.101 --> 13:31.835
But whatever reservations
you have,

13:32.445 --> 13:34.822
you leave them here today.

13:35.561 --> 13:38.002
Or I will leave you back
the way you were in Cuba.

13:46.354 --> 13:48.150
Avi.

13:50.497 --> 13:52.213
Whoa.

13:52.702 --> 13:55.533
Oh, oh, goodness.

13:57.984 --> 14:00.283
Who might we have here?

14:02.632 --> 14:05.102
Avi, meet parissa,
it's an old acquaintance

14:05.220 --> 14:06.991
turned new associate.

14:07.093 --> 14:09.727
My dear, you are a vision.

14:09.829 --> 14:11.796
It's nice to meet you, avi.

14:11.898 --> 14:13.392
Persian, eh?

14:13.684 --> 14:15.260
Very good.

14:15.659 --> 14:17.986
I spent some time in Tehran

14:18.071 --> 14:19.537
back in the '70s.

14:19.654 --> 14:21.056
What a city.

14:21.141 --> 14:23.550
It makes me very
sad, you know, what's happening

14:23.635 --> 14:24.963
between our two countries.

14:25.048 --> 14:27.161
Ah, yeah, I couldn't agree more.

14:27.246 --> 14:28.946
And I'd like
to hear all of your thoughts

14:29.065 --> 14:30.135
on this matter.

14:30.220 --> 14:32.187
And I would like to tell you.

14:32.272 --> 14:35.140
But I think Theodore would like

14:35.225 --> 14:36.724
some time with you first.

14:36.809 --> 14:38.476
Then I guess Theodore

14:38.561 --> 14:40.360
and I should chat.

14:40.664 --> 14:42.291
- Muir?
- Hmm?

14:42.415 --> 14:44.267
All morning, we've been

14:44.352 --> 14:47.019
enjoying my cellar.

14:47.333 --> 14:49.867
Help yourself
to whatever you please.

14:49.952 --> 14:52.181
Thank you.

14:54.674 --> 14:57.007
Oh, to be a young man.

14:57.110 --> 14:59.135
You are a young man.

14:59.220 --> 15:00.520
Mm-hmm.

15:00.610 --> 15:02.676
I kept the party going.

15:02.990 --> 15:04.556
Someone spiked

15:04.641 --> 15:06.517
the entire Saint wedding

15:06.602 --> 15:08.650
with LSD last night.

15:09.020 --> 15:11.885
Seriously?
Was it you?

15:12.299 --> 15:14.002
Not this time.

15:16.462 --> 15:17.963
Okay.

15:18.048 --> 15:21.385
I'm not gonna, uh, take up
too much of your time.

15:21.868 --> 15:24.478
I am about to be
in a position to triple

15:24.595 --> 15:26.121
the number of guns
that are headed south.

15:26.205 --> 15:28.339
I need to know that you can
handle that kind of weight.

15:28.423 --> 15:30.089
When have I ever let you down?

15:30.174 --> 15:31.807
Honestly, avi, all the time.

15:31.892 --> 15:33.775
There were always good reasons
for any hiccups.

15:33.860 --> 15:36.297
This is it, it's the final push.

15:36.791 --> 15:38.215
The sandinistas are hurting.

15:38.317 --> 15:40.939
This will break their back.
I want this war sewn up.

15:41.024 --> 15:43.627
On to bigger
and better things, eh?

15:44.095 --> 15:45.222
Triple the guns

15:45.324 --> 15:47.385
in 60 days... say you can do it.

15:47.736 --> 15:49.627
You have the money,
you'll have the guns,

15:49.729 --> 15:52.056
I swear, but I do hope

15:52.141 --> 15:54.007
the end of this war
will not mean

15:54.092 --> 15:55.908
the end of our business?

15:59.352 --> 16:01.290
With everything you know about
me, and you really don't think

16:01.374 --> 16:03.153
there's gonna be another war
just around the corner?

16:06.255 --> 16:07.721
Come have a drink.

16:07.847 --> 16:09.880
- Come on.
- If you say so.

16:27.147 --> 16:28.681
How is he?

16:30.120 --> 16:31.687
He's fucked up.

16:31.851 --> 16:33.250
Bullet got his spine.

16:33.439 --> 16:35.072
Doc said he ain't walking again.

16:35.165 --> 16:36.517
Fuck.

16:38.594 --> 16:40.294
But he's gonna live?

16:40.914 --> 16:41.976
I'm gonna assume

16:42.061 --> 16:43.894
that you didn't know
anything about this?

16:44.068 --> 16:46.775
That this was just cops
being cops?

16:46.869 --> 16:48.709
Or is there some shit
that you want to tell me?

16:56.409 --> 16:58.619
You can't be fucking serious.

16:58.737 --> 17:00.268
Okay, okay.

17:00.353 --> 17:02.306
Yeah, I came here
for a little compassion.

17:02.782 --> 17:04.174
Why did I think
I'd get anything

17:04.259 --> 17:06.539
- but a world of shit from you?
- I'm sorry Eddie is dead,

17:06.635 --> 17:08.111
okay, I am.

17:08.512 --> 17:10.252
But I'm not letting you see them

17:10.337 --> 17:12.557
- when you're in this state.
- What state, Sharon? I'm upset.

17:12.641 --> 17:14.406
Come on,
you're fucking high, Beau!

17:14.499 --> 17:15.549
You think I don't see it?

17:15.682 --> 17:17.215
I want to see my fucking kids.
- You think I don't know?

17:17.300 --> 17:19.233
- And I'm not gonna say it again.
- Or what?

17:21.786 --> 17:23.551
You gonna hit me?

17:23.637 --> 17:24.760
Hmm?

17:26.426 --> 17:27.727
After they find cocaine

17:27.811 --> 17:30.413
or-or whatever it is you're on
in your blood?

17:30.894 --> 17:33.431
You want to make sure
you never see your kids again?

17:34.060 --> 17:36.150
That's the way
to make sure it happens.

17:36.454 --> 17:38.361
